    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5618" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Κύθηρα</span></b> , pl.:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">Cythēra</span>, an island off the coast of Laconia, S.W. of
          the promontory of Malēa, where the worship of Aphrodite had been
          introduced by an early Phoenician colony, <i><span class="en">Od.
            9.81</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 15.432</span></i>. —<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Κυθηρόθεν</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">from Cythēra</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 15.538</span></i>. —Adj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Κυθήριος</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">of Cythēra</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 10.268</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            15.431</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
